title: What time is Strictly Come Dancing's results show tonight and who's left so far?
text:
Whose time on the Strictly dancefloor will be over this week? (Picture: BBC)

Strictly Come Dancing delivered another awesome show on Saturday night – bringing yet more perfect 10s to the dancefloor as the 12 remaining celebrities returned.

With last weekend’s show seeing some huge scores and the first 10s of the series, the pressure was on for the couples to impress once again this week – which they duly did, with a stunning salsa from Karim and Amy, Mike Bushell reviving the Carlton Dance and Will Bayley’s routine leaving Motsi Mabuse too overcome to speak.

Sadly another pair will be bidding farewell on Sunday night – but what time should you tune in?

Here’s what you need to know…

What time is Strictly Come Dancing’s results show on tonight?

Strictly Come Dancing’s results show kicks off – as it has in recent weeks – on BBC One on Sunday night at 7.15pm.

Saffon and AJ took the lead at the top of the scoreboard after their foxtrot (Picture: BBC)

It’s a 45-minute show once again ahead of Antiques Roadshow at 8pm.

Advertisement

Advertisement

As well as revealing the next couple to be booted off the dancefloor following this week’s dance-off, Sunday’s show will also feature a performance from chart star Mabel.

How many celebrities have been eliminated from the series so far?

Dianne was visibly upset after last weekend’s elimination (Picture: BBC)

So far we have bid farewell to three celebrities this series.

The first out was James Cracknell, who left in week two with dance partner Luba Mushtuk, while next out was Anneka Rice and her pro partner Kevin Clifton.

Dev Griffin and Dianne Buswell left last Sunday – sparking controversy after viewers claimed they had been unable to vote for the Radio 1 DJ, who was tipped as one of the favourites to win.

Who was top of the leaderboard in Strictly this weekend?

This weekend saw a new couple top the Strictly leaderboard as Saffron Barker and AJ Pritchard led the way ahead of the others.

The pair nabbed their first perfect 10 of the series as they closed the show with a spectacular foxtrot to Frank Sinatra classic New York New York.

‘I think she did really, really well. This is a big iconic song that needs a big personality to fill it in, and I think you lived up to that song,’ Motsi Mabuse told them.

‘You gave me beautiful technique, you gave me music, you gave me everything I needed to end the show. Congratulations.’

Guest judge Alfonso Ribeiro added: ‘That was awesome. Your rise and fall was spectacular. I loved it, you hit it with a bang.’

description: Strictly Come Dancing is set to bid farewell to another celebrity couple on Sunday night - but what time should you tune in?
